OL,7,F"This may be because of an increase in
OL,8,Fthe number of employers offering
OL,9,Finsurance as an incentive, insurers
OL,10,Fmarketing their products in different
OL,11,Fways and to different potential
OL,12,Fcustomers, or due to worries about NHS
OL,13,Fwaiting lists and the length of time
OL,14,Fit could take to be seen."
OL,16,FBrett Hill, the head of health and
OL,17,Fprotection at the consultancy
OL,18,FBroadstone, told the i that the NHS
OL,19,Fcrisis was prompting more workers to
OL,20,Ftake up membership, with price
OL,21,Fincreases "historically high".
